* :YFCYcsURQbIiVcpW: A fundamental property of a language is that the meaning of its tokens are shared \cite{finin1999agent}.  A language also exists to serve a purpose.  ``Agents need an \textit{Agent Communication Language} (ACL) in order to interact in a shared language, hiding the details of their internals and to build communities of agents that can tackle problems that no individual agent can.''
